quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  2,38,"We said, ´Go down from it, every one of you! Then when guidance comes to you from Me, those who follow My guidance will feel no fear and will know no sorrow.´"
  2,39,"But those who are kafir and deny Our Signs are the Companions of the Fire, remaining in it timelessly, for ever"
  2,40,Tribe of Israel! remember the blessing I conferred on you. Honour My contract and I will honour your contract. Have dread of Me alone
  2,41,"Have iman in what I have sent down, confirming what is with you. Do not be the first to reject it and do not sell My Signs for a paltry price. Have taqwa of Me alone"
  2,42,Do not mix up truth with falsehood and knowingly hide the truth
  2,43,Establish salat and pay zakat and bow with those who bow
  2,44,"Do you order people to devoutness and forget yourselves, when you recite the Book? Will you not use your intellect"
  2,45,"Seek help in steadfastness and salat. But that is a very hard thing, except for the humble"
  2,46,those who are aware that they will meet their Lord and that they will return to Him
  2,47,Tribe of Israel! remember the blessing I conferred on you and that I preferred you over all other beings
  2,48,"Have fear of a Day when no self will be able to compensate for another in any way. No intercession will be taken from it, no ransom taken from it, and none will be helped"